Southern Maya Mountains, Bladen Nature Reserve, Ek Xux Canyon, mountains 2 airline km northeast of the Ek Xux archeological site. Steep canyon slope dominated by short forest (2-8 m tall) of slender trees of Theaceae, Myrtaceae, Ericaceae, and Clusia, with a thick humus layer, and a herbaceous understory dominated by Rhynchospora exaltata and Ichnanthus mexicana, with very rare taller trees of Pinus; soil derived from volcanic rocks.
